40|$|This Article {{examines}} {{whether the}} current penalties in the United States Sentencing Guidelines are {{set at the}} appropriate levels to deter cartels optimally The authors analyze two data sets to determine how high on average <b>cartels</b> raise <b>prices.</b> The first consists of every published scholarly economic study {{of the effects of}} <b>cartels</b> on <b>prices</b> in individual cases. The second consists of every final verdict in a US. antitrust case in which a neutral finder of fact reported collusive overcharges. They report average overcharges of 49...|$|R
